	<h2> Notable scientific work:</h2>
	<div>
		<ul>
			<li><b>Theory of relativity and E = mcÂ²</b> - reconciles Maxwell's equations for electricity and magnetism with the laws of mechanics, by introducing major changes to mechanics close to the speed of light. This later became known as Einstein's special theory of relativity.</li>
			<li style="list-style:none;">&nbsp;</li>
			<li><b>Photons and energy quanta</b> -  Einstein proposed that light consists of localized particles</li>
			<li style="list-style:none;">&nbsp;</li>
			<li><b>Wormholes</b> - Wormhole, in physics, is a hypothetical feature of space and time continuum that is a path through the continuum itself.</li>
		</ul>
	</div>
